== Overview ==
The '''Gamma Sector''' (commonly referred to simply as '''Gamma''') is the third and most advanced outland zone available to [[Controller|Controllers]], and serves as the primary late-game destination. It is a sprawling, dangerous frontier beyond the [[Talsian Warfront]] — designed explicitly for Controllers who have already established themselves in [[Talsia]] and are pushing for end-game progression. Unlike Vulcore or Talsia, Gamma is deliberately non-linear: the four quadrants each have their own themes, rewards, and hazards, and Controllers are free to choose where to spend their [[KCharge]] based on their goals.

Gamma was designed to be a '''high-risk, high-reward''' environment. Whereas Talsia rewarded building a "tank everything" squad, Gamma punishes it. Controllers who rely on deflection-heavy, slow squads will find themselves penalised both in combat effectiveness and in experience rewards. Instead, Gamma favours '''speed, fire rate, and precise target prioritisation'''. The enemy will drain and destroy you before you can react if you're not fast enough.

