Gamma is entered directly from the [[Workshop]] at no [[KCharge]] cost. Leaving and re-entering is free — this freedom to quickly refit and re-enter is an intentional design choice, enabling Controllers to adapt their loadout between patrol runs without a KC tax.

== Prerequisites ==
Gamma is an endgame zone. The intended progression before entering Gamma is:
* '''[[Talsian Warfront|Talsia]] Alpha Sector''' firmly established
* '''[[Advanced Multi-Fire Director|AMFDs]]''' equipped on squad bots
* '''[[Raven]]''' chassis unlocked — the Raven is unlocked at '''18,000 TRP''' and is the primary chassis for Gamma
* A solid supply of [[Accolade|Accolades]] to hire mercenaries at the Epsilon FOB
* At least 100–200 million credits for a new [[Workshop]] upgrade (9th bot slot) and initial Raven chassis purchases

The [[Raven]] is the defining chassis of Gamma. While it is possible to enter Gamma without Ravens, doing so is generally considered dangerous — the enemies are tuned around opponent squads of the late-game tier.

== Theme ==
The Gamma Sector is a multi-environment frontier region defined by:
* '''Praetorian territory''' — a disciplined, advanced military faction guarding vast meteorite mining operations across the SE and NE quadrants
* '''Ancient Horus civilization''' — ruins of a lost alien/ancient culture, including Temples, Ziggurats, and sacred city-planets accessible via portal and spaceship
* '''Lava Fields and Volcanic Forts''' — a fire-themed SW quadrant dominated by the '''Lords of the Flame''', their Lava Reapers, Flaming Patrols, and the deadly Carnutum Ignus Arena
* '''Outer Space and Pirates''' — the NW quadrant expands into actual space, where Pirate Corvettes, Pirate Scorpions, and wandering Space Pirates await
* '''Ex-Federate remnants''' — former Federate military who have set up mining operations and special forces in the NW
* A deliberate philosophy of '''exploration and discovery''' — Gamma rewards Controllers who read carefully, take notes, and follow quest breadcrumbs across all four quadrants

== Progression Guide ==
{{MessageBox
| header = Progression Guide
| text   = For a detailed walkthrough and strategy guide covering patrol phases, squad setups, and quest steps, see the '''[[Gamma Sector Guide]]'''. The information below provides a condensed overview. See the individual quadrant sections for related context.
}}

A condensed progression path for transitioning into Gamma:
# Reach 18,000 TRP in [[Talsia]] and unlock the [[Raven]] chassis
# Run Vulcore cash farming patrol to accumulate 100–200M credits
# Purchase the 9th bot [[Workshop]] upgrade and additional [[Raven]] chassis (up to 2 initially)
# Enter Gamma and head to the [[#Epsilon Forward Operating Base|Epsilon FOB]] — familiarise yourself with available mercs and items
# Once confident, move to the '''SE quadrant''' for Praetorian Bases, Research Labs, and Hornet/Warthog chassis unlocks
# Explore NE and SW quadrants for quests, unique chassis, and special rewards
# Pursue the [[#The Brotherhood of the Chosen Quest|Brotherhood of the Chosen Quest]] across all four quadrants for the [[Peace Maker Cannon]]

== Epsilon Forward Operating Base ==
[[File:Epsilonbase.jpg|thumb|right|280px|The Epsilon Forward Operating Base — the Controller's hub in Gamma.]]
The '''Epsilon Forward Operating Base''' (commonly called the '''Epsilon FOB''' or simply '''Gamma Base''') is the Controller's hub within Gamma Sector. It serves as the primary source of mercenaries, special equipment, and currency exchange services.

The Epsilon FOB is accessed at the start of any Gamma patrol. Mercs hired at the Epsilon FOB persist with the squad for the entire patrol — unlike Talsia where mercs are hired before each mission and released afterwards, Gamma mercs stay with the squad until they are killed in combat or you return to the workshop. This makes each merc hire a significant investment: losing them in a bad fight means losing all the Accolades you spent.

