=== North East Quadrant ===
[[File:Ne_gen1.jpg|thumb|right|240px|The NE quadrant — Tons of sand. It’s coarse and rough and irritating... and it gets everywhere.]]

The North East quadrant is the quest and exploration hub of Gamma Sector. It is home to ancient '''Horus Temples''' that contain vital quest information, secret chambers, and powerful rewards locked behind puzzles and rune knowledge. Praetorian forces defend both the open terrain and the temple grounds.

'''Key features:'''
* '''Horus Temple''' — the centrepiece of the NE. Contains books, inscriptions, a secret portal, and the Brotherhood door code needed for the [[#Peace Maker Cannon Quest|PMC quest]]. Also contains a '''4-digit dial''' that opens a '''Pharaoh's Tomb''' for rewards. Requires the four [[Runes]] to have been obtained to access the portal chamber (the Runes must be ''in the workshop'' — they do not need to be physically equipped unless the Ziggurat is the target).
* '''Enhanced Reaper Quest Portal''' — inside the Horus Temple, a portal appears ''only'' if the Controller has already received the city name from a SE outpost. The portal leads to the correct city on the Horus Planet, where 3 battles must be won to obtain the [[Enhanced Reaper]].
* '''Matriarch (PMC Quest)''' — an NE Matriarch who provides the city name needed for the PMC quest (requires already having the Knight's name from the SE outpost)
* '''Terminus Prototype Chassis Trader''' — a special chassis trader in the NE who will sell the [[Terminus Prototype]] chassis, but '''only if the Prius merc is hired and present in the squad'''
* '''Antenna Hacking events''' — hacking Praetorian communications antennas can yield Mirons, experience bonuses, or other random rewards
* '''Brotherhood of the Chosen clues''' — quest information is distributed across the NE (temple inscriptions, Matriarch dialogue); reading and recording this information carefully is essential

'''Enemies encountered:'''
* Horus enemy units

'''Rewards:'''
* [[Enhanced Reaper]] chassis (quest reward)
* [[Terminus Prototype]] chassis (via trader + Prius merc)
* Mirons (via Antenna hacking and other events)
* Quest information (Brotherhood code, Matriarch city name)

