=== South East Quadrant ===
[[File:SE_generic3.jpg|thumb|right|240px]]

The South East quadrant is the '''primary experience-grinding zone''' in Gamma Sector and contains the most lucrative activities for mid-to-late Gamma progression. It is defined by the massive Praetorian Mining Facilities that extract rare '''Meteorite Iron''' from the sector's deposits, and by the Praetorian military presence protecting those operations.

'''Key features:'''
* '''Praetorian Mining Facilities''' — the centrepiece of the SE. These facilities actively mine Meteorite Iron that Controllers can '''steal''' by hiring Cargo Transport mercs from the Epsilon FOB (see [[#Meteorite Iron Mining|Meteorite Iron Mining]]). Stealing from these facilities yields colossal amounts of experience and Mirons.
* '''Praetorian Bases & Research Labs''' — as in the NE, defeating SE Research Labs yields [[Hornet]]/[[Warthog]] chassis schematics
* '''Reinforcement mercs''' — Controllers can call for patrol reinforcements while in the SE. There is approximately a '''5% chance''' of receiving free reinforcement mercs, a '''35% chance''' of the call being intercepted (triggering an enemy attack instead), and the remainder resulting in no response
* '''Casino & Market''' — the SE has both a Casino and a Market. The Market is encountered fairly frequently & offers Pneumatron Reactors for a whopping 10,000 Accolades

'''The Wasp problem:''' The single biggest combat challenge in the SE (and NE) is the [[Wasp]] enemy unit. Wasps have a base speed of '''225''' and are equipped with powerful drain weapons. At high BM (37M+), squads can encounter 4–6 Wasps in a single fight. Against a Reaper-and-Rayden drain build, Wasps can deflect drain entirely if they're accompanied by Praetorian units carrying [[DAX Pod]] modules. The primary counter strategies are:
* '''Out-speed them''' — equip at least one Immobilizer on each Raven (base 150 speed) to gain targeting priority and drain/kill 2+ Wasps before they fire
* '''Bring Vamper mercs''' — Vamper mercs can drain multiple Wasps simultaneously, especially useful when Wasps are spread out
* '''Lower BM''' — keeping squad BM around 20–30M reduces the number of Wasps encountered per fight

'''Enemies encountered:'''
* Praetorian units (large numbers; 3–7 per encounter depending on BM)
* Wasp units (drain specialists; primary threat)
* Praetorian Recon (highly dangerous!)
* Raiders

'''Rewards:'''
* Massive experience bonuses (base fight exp + High Priority Target Reward)
* Mirons (from Meteorite delivery)
* [[Hornet]] / [[Recon Hornet]] / [[Warthog]] / [[Recon Warthog]] chassis schematics
* Cash (significant credits per fight)

