=== South West Quadrant ===
[[File:Lavaflow.jpg|thumb|right|240px|(Placeholder Image) The SW quadrant — volcanic lava fields and Praetorian fire installations.]]

The South West quadrant is the most atmospheric area of Gamma Sector — a volcanic, lava-scorched region dominated by the '''Lords of the Flame''', a fire-themed faction operating Lava Forts and Lava Temples. The SW is the primary source of '''Lava Diamonds''', the unique Flaming Hornet chassis, and the critical '''Coin of Destiny''' needed for the PMC quest.

'''Key features:'''
* '''Lava Forts''' — heavily fortified positions defended by Lava Reapers and fire-themed units. Defeating a Lava Fort yields [[Lava Diamonds]] and, importantly, the '''Coin of Destiny''' (required as step 4 of the [[#Peace Maker Cannon Quest|PMC quest]]). The [[Flaming Hornet]] chassis schematics are also dropped from Lava Forts.
* '''Lava Temples''' — ancient fire temples containing additional Lava Diamond caches and possible quest-related artefacts
* '''SW Caves''' — cave systems below the lava fields containing [[Lava Diamonds]] and [[Mirons]]. Encounters inside can include Lava Reapers paired with Sentinels and Bulwarks.
* '''[[Carnutum Ignus Arena]] (Lava Arena)''' — the SW Arena is the Gamma equivalent of Talsia's [[Master Controllers]]. Defeating the '''Arena Masters''' awards the [[Hydroplasmonic|Hydroplasmonic Reactor]] — a top-tier endgame reactor. The Arena can also yield Lava Diamonds through wagering.
* '''Flaming Hornet''' — a fire-variant of the [[Hornet]] chassis, dropped exclusively from Lava Forts in the SW

'''Enemies encountered:'''
* Lava Reapers (fire-variant Reaper; very dangerous; high fire rate)
* Flaming Patrols
* Praetorian units (mixed)
* Cave-specific enemies (Lava Reapers with Sentinels, Raiders)
* Arena combatants (CyBulwark and champion bots for Arena Master fights)

'''Rewards:'''
* [[Lava Diamond|Lava Diamonds]] (from Forts, Temples, Caves)
* [[Flaming Hornet]] chassis schematics (from Lava Forts)
* [[Coin of Destiny]] (PMC quest item — from first Lava Fort defeat)
* [[Hydroplasmonic|Hydroplasmonic Reactor]] (from Arena Masters completion)
* Mirons (from SW Caves)

