=== North West Quadrant ===
[[File:Gammasector.jpg|thumb|right|240px|The NW quadrant — outer space operations and Ex-Feds territory.]]

The North West quadrant is the most accessible entry point for Controllers just arriving in Gamma, since it contains [[Destroyer|Destroyers]] and [[Battle Cruiser|Battle Cruisers]] that award [[Talsian Rank Points|TRP]] and [[Accolade|Accolades]] — familiar content from Talsia. Beyond this, the NW expands dramatically into '''outer space''', hosting Pirate operations, a spaceport, and the final stage of the PMC quest.

'''Key features:'''
* '''Destroyers & Battle Cruisers''' — the safe, familiar content of the NW. Destroyers award 25 TRP + 15 Accolades. Battle Cruisers award 75 TRP. '''[[True Guard]]''' units also appear in the NW and award Accolades (a notable change from Talsia where TG was the primary bottleneck).
* '''Ex-Feds (Ex-Federates)''' — former Federate military forces who have set up independent operations in the NW, including:
** '''Ex-Feds Mining Operations Camp''' — a Federate mining installation; engaging it yields significant Accolade rewards
** '''Ex-Feds Base''' — a larger fortified Ex-Feds installation; defeating it yields 100–200 Accolades
** '''Ex-Feds Special Operations''' — elite Ex-Feds squads; very dangerous (high deflection from Uplink Trucks; can instantly wipe Ravens if out-sped)
* '''NW Caves''' — cave systems containing [[Miron|Mirons]] (the primary accessible Miron source early in Gamma); valuable for building up the Miron supply before meteorite mining becomes feasible
* '''Pirate Corvettes''' — Space Pirates operating Corvette-class vessels in the NW and outer space. Defeating Pirate Corvettes contributes to the '''Pirate Hunter''' (50 kills) and '''Pirate Exterminator''' (100 kills) stat milestones. Corvette count is tracked across the entire set.
* '''Pirate Scorpions''' — elite Pirate units deploying Scorpion-class chassis with heavy drain deflection. Up to 4 Pirate Scorpions can appear in a single encounter; a full squad of 4 can be effectively invincible against standard drain (deflecting 29,400 drain vs a standard Rayden crit of ~29,250). DAX Pods were previously given to Scorpions but have since been replaced with Gravity Hydro Boosters to bring their drain deflection to a manageable level.
* '''Currency Traders''' — the NW hosts traders where currencies can be exchanged (e.g. Mercreds to Mirons). However, each exchange costs KC and only converts a limited amount per visit, making bulk conversion very expensive.
* '''[[#Rayden (NW Trader)|Rayden Weapon Trader]]''' — the NW trader sells the [[Rayden Device]] drain weapon
* '''Brotherhood Outpost (PMC Quest)''' — found in the NW only after obtaining the [[Coin of Destiny]] from the SW. Requires entering the correct Brotherhood door code (from NE temple inscriptions). Selecting the correct Knight inside triggers the next phase of the PMC quest.
* '''Airfield (PMC Quest)''' — the spaceship launch site found in the NW after the Knight joins the squad. The Knight pilots the ship to the Horus Planet for the PMC quest finale.
* '''Space Monster''' — a unique and very dangerous enemy encountered in outer space; notable for being an unexpected surprise for Controllers who venture too far out

'''Enemies encountered:'''
* Ex-Feds Special Ops (walkers; very high deflection; can one-shot Ravens)
* [[Destroyer]] (warship; 25 TRP + 15 Accolades)
* [[Battle Cruiser]] (warship; 75 TRP; requires preparation)
* [[True Guard]] units (now award Accolades in Gamma)
* Pirate Corvettes (space pirates; contribute to Corvette kill count)
* Pirate Scorpions (very dangerous; heavy drain deflection)
* Space Monster (unique encounter)

'''Rewards:'''
* [[Talsian Rank Points|TRP]] (from Destroyers, Battle Cruisers)
* [[Accolade|Accolades]] (from TG, Ex-Feds Outposts, Destroyers, Battle Cruisers)
* [[Miron|Mirons]] (from NW Caves)
* [[Rayden Device]] weapon (from NW Trader)
* Pirate kill count milestones (50 = Pirate Hunter; 100 = Pirate Exterminator)

