== Chassis Available in Gamma ==
Gamma Sector introduces six new chassis that are unavailable anywhere else in the game.

=== Hornet / Recon Hornet ===
<gallery widths="160" heights="120">
File:Hornet.jpg|[[Hornet]] chassis
File:Reconhornet.jpg|[[Recon Hornet]] variant
</gallery>

The [[Hornet]] is the primary new chassis introduced in Gamma and serves as the Seer-equivalent offensive fast-attack bot. Hornets are unlocked via schematics dropped from '''Praetorian Bases and Research Labs''' in the SE and NE quadrants. The Recon Hornet is simply a cosmetic variant of the Hornet.

=== Warthog / Recon Warthog ===
<gallery widths="160" heights="120">
File:Warthog.jpg|[[Warthog]] chassis
File:Reconwarthog.jpg|[[Recon Warthog]] chassis
</gallery>

The [[Warthog]] is the Sentinel-equivalent chassis introduced in Gamma — a heavier, more defensive alternative to the Hornet. Like the Hornet, it is obtained from schematics in '''Praetorian Bases and Research Labs''' in the SE and NE. Controllers choosing between Hornet and Warthog schematics must make a one-time pick per unlock opportunity (similar to the Master Controller chassis choice in Talsia). The Recon Warthog is an enhanced variant with 1 more Shield equipment slot (5 vs 4).

=== Flaming Hornet ===
[[File:Flaminghornet.jpg|thumb|right|220px|The Flaming Hornet — a fire-enhanced variant exclusive to the SW.]]

The [[Flaming Hornet]] is a fire-themed variant of the Hornet chassis, exclusive to the South West quadrant. It is obtained from schematics dropped by '''Lava Forts''' in the SW.

=== Enhanced Reaper ===
[[File:Enhancedreaper.jpg|thumb|right|220px|The Enhanced Reaper — a stolen prototype obtained via the NE quest.]]

The [[Enhanced Reaper]] is a modified, upgraded version of the standard [[Reaper]] chassis, referred to in-game as a "stolen prototype." It is obtained by completing a multi-step quest primarily focused in the NE quadrant (see [[#Enhanced Reaper Quest|Enhanced Reaper Quest]] below).

Key improvements over the standard Reaper:
* '''200% drain bonus''' (enhanced from standard Reaper drain)
* '''Extra module slot''' (giving it more flexibility than a standard Reaper)

=== Terminus Prototype ===
[[File:Terminus.jpg|thumb|right|220px|The Terminus Prototype — available from the NE chassis trader.]]

The [[Terminus Prototype]] is a special chassis available from a '''chassis trader in the NE quadrant'''. To access this trader and unlock the Terminus Prototype, the Controller must have the '''Prius''' merc present in their squad. The Prius is found via NE exploration events and joins the squad for free.

=== CyBulwark ===
[[File:Cybulwark.jpg|thumb|right|220px|The CyBulwark — Gamma's Arena Champion chassis.]]

The [[CyBulwark]] is a unique Arena Champion chassis created by the '''Lords of the Flame''' using Praetorian technology and renegade AI, designed specifically for combat in the '''Carnutum Ignus Arena'''. It is an unusual hybrid design that merges multiple ability sets into a single weapons platform.

== Meteorite Iron Mining ==
[[File:Meteoriteiron.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Meteorite Iron — stolen from Praetorian Mining Facilities in the SE.]]

One of Gamma's most distinctive and rewarding activities is '''stealing Meteorite Iron''' from Praetorian Mining Facilities in the '''SE quadrant'''. This activity provides some of the highest experience-per-patrol output in the entire game.

'''How it works:'''
# Hire '''Cargo Transport''' mercs at the Epsilon FOB before entering the SE (up to 4 at a time; each costs Accolades)
# Locate Praetorian Mining Facilities during your SE patrol
# Defeat the Praetorian defenders and proceed with the extraction
# Each Cargo Transport delivers '''5 tons''' of Meteorite Iron per run
# Upon delivery, the Cargo Transport mercs are '''consumed''' (lost from the squad)
# The reward is granted: massive experience + Mirons proportional to the total tons delivered

'''Example deliveries from early testing:'''
* 100 tons delivered → ~60,000,000 experience points + 1,503 Mirons
* 234 tons delivered → ~58,500,000 experience points + 5,850 Mirons

{{MessageBox|header=Nerf Notice|text=This has since been nerfed, as you can only hire up to 4 Cargo Transports at a time, thus delivering only up to 20 tons per trip.}}

=== The 100-Ton Threshold: Pirates Start Hunting You ===
{{MessageBox|header=Work in Progress|text=Exact details of the pirate aggression mechanic — the specific timing and magnitude of pre-drain/pre-damage — are yet to be confirmed. Figures above are based on community observations.}}

After a Controller has collectively stolen '''100 or more tons''' of Meteorite Iron from the Praetorian Mining Facilities, the '''Space Pirates''' take notice. From this point onward, Pirates begin '''pre-draining and pre-damaging''' the squad's reactors and shields at the start of encounters — effectively getting a "free turn" against the squad before combat even begins. This makes all subsequent Gamma patrols riskier, and Controllers must account for this "head start" penalty when planning their loadouts and patrol lengths.

This mechanic is a significant shift: the more you steal from the Praetorians, the more dangerous every patrol becomes. [[DAX Pod]] modules become relevant again at this stage — their drain recovery properties help mitigate the pre-patrol reactor drain that Pirates inflict before each fight.

== Space Pirates ==
[[File:Piratescorpions.jpg|thumb|right|240px|Pirate Scorpions — some of the most formidable enemies in Gamma.]]

Space Pirates are a faction operating primarily in the '''NW quadrant''' and outer space regions of Gamma Sector. They range from skirmishing Corvette patrols to the fearsome Pirate Scorpion squadrons.

=== Pirate Corvettes ===

[[File:Corvette_turret.png|thumb|right|150px|(Placeholder Image) Pirate Corvette turret]]
Pirate Corvettes are the standard combat vessel of the Pirates. Defeating Pirate Corvettes contributes to permanent stat milestones:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Kills !! Milestone !! Notes
|-
| '''50 kills''' || '''Pirate Hunter''' || Tracked on the Controller's stats page
|-
| '''100 kills''' || '''Pirate Exterminator''' || Tracked on the Controller's stats page
|}

=== Pirate Scorpions ===

Pirate Scorpions are elite Pirate units with Scorpion-chassis configurations and extremely high drain deflection. A squad of '''4 Pirate Scorpions''' was originally nearly unbeatable due to their combined drain deflection exceeding the damage output of a standard Rayden crit (29,400 deflection vs ~29,250 Rayden crit drain). Their loadout was subsequently adjusted — replacing [[DAX Pod]] modules with [[Gravity Hydro Booster]] modules — to bring their deflection to a manageable level while keeping them dangerous. They remain one of the hardest enemy configurations in Gamma.

== Quests ==

Gamma Sector contains several multi-step quests that span multiple quadrants. Unlike most Talsia content, quest information in Gamma is '''procedurally generated and set-specific''' — quest keys, city names, and Knight names are '''randomised each set''' and differ between accounts. Controllers must read all event text carefully and record information, as most quest trigger events are one-time-only.

{{MessageBox|header=Work in Progress|text=Some quest steps are still undocumented or subject to change between sets. Quest information is based on the initial set of testing and early community reports.}}

=== The Brotherhood of the Chosen — Peace Maker Cannon Quest ===
[[File:Peacemakercannon.jpg|thumb|right|220px|The Peace Maker Cannon — awarded on completing the Brotherhood Quest.]]

The Brotherhood of the Chosen is the primary quest of Gamma Sector, spanning all four quadrants and requiring careful, systematic play across multiple patrols. Its reward is the '''[[Peace Maker Cannon]]''' — the most powerful weapon in the game.

'''Peace Maker Cannon stats:'''
* Shield Damage: 4,750 | Armour Damage: 2,000 | Radius: 5 | Accuracy: 100% | SPT: 1 | Energy per shot: 1,000
* '''Special Edition Peace Maker Cannon''' (first completion only): Shield Damage: 4,950 | Armour Damage: 2,025 | Radius: 5 | Accuracy: 100% | SPT: 1 | Energy per shot: 950 | Tech: 1,000

'''Quest steps (in order):'''

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Step !! Location !! Action !! Notes
|-
| '''1''' || South East || Find the **Knight's name** at an SE Outpost || ~10% chance per outpost encounter; a unique set-specific name is randomly generated
|-
| '''2''' || North East || Find the **city name** from the NE Matriarch || Only available after Step 1 is complete; ~5% chance per Matriarch encounter; a unique set-specific city name is generated
|-
| '''3''' || North East || Find the **Brotherhood door code** from inscriptions in the Horus Temple || Read the temple inscriptions carefully — this is a one-time event; the code is required in Step 5
|-
| '''4''' || South West || Obtain the **Coin of Destiny** by defeating the Lava Fort in SW || Only the first Lava Fort defeat yields the Coin; subsequent Lava Forts give only Lava Diamonds
|-
| '''5''' || North West || With the Coin of Destiny, find the **Brotherhood Outpost** during NW patrol; enter the correct door code; select the **correct Knight** || The correct Knight is the one whose name matches Step 1; hiring this Knight is free and he joins the squad
|-
| '''6''' || North West || Find the **Airfield** in the NW (appears after the Knight joins); let the Knight pilot the spaceship to the **Horus Planet** || Airfield appears during standard NW patrol once the Knight is in the squad
|-
| '''7''' || Horus Planet || Travel to the Horus Planet and find the city matching Step 2 || The portal leads to the city; explore to find the Matriarch
|-
| '''8''' || Horus Planet || Learn from the city's Matriarch that the PMC was **stolen by Pirates** || 
|-
| '''9''' || Horus Planet || **Raze the Pirate Outpost** on the Horus Planet to recover the Peace Maker Cannon || Defeating the Pirate Outpost completes the quest
|}

'''Reward:''' The '''first Controller''' to complete the quest each set receives the '''Special Edition Peace Maker Cannon''' (slightly superior stats). All subsequent completions receive the standard [[Peace Maker Cannon]].

'''Brotherhood Knights after quest completion:''' After completing the PMC quest, the Brotherhood Outpost can still be visited and additional Knights can be hired.

