== Reward Mechanics ==

=== Experience Scaling ===
Gamma experience rewards do not scale simply with BM the way Vulcore and Talsia do. The Gamma reward formula includes several modifiers:

'''BM Penalty (applied above 30M BM):'''
{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Total BM !! XP Multiplier
|-
| ≤ 30,000,000 || 100% (no penalty)
|-
| 30,000,001 – 35,000,000 || 90%
|-
| 35,000,001 – 40,000,000 || 80%
|-
| 40,000,001 – 45,000,000 || 70%
|-
| 45,000,001 – 50,000,000 || 60%
|-
| > 50,000,000 || 50%
|}

'''Optimal BM for Gamma:''' Approximately '''20–30 million BM''' maximises Gamma rewards while keeping enemy squad sizes manageable. Controllers with 37M+ BM will regularly face 4–6 Wasp squads and the full BM penalty above.

=== Mirons ===
{{MessageBox|header=Work in Progress|text=Miron usage is not fully documented. Known sources include: NW Caves, Meteorite Iron delivery rewards, NE Antenna hacking events, NE Currency Trader, and various patrol events.}}

Mirons are a Gamma-specific currency. Known acquisition sources include NW Caves, Meteorite Iron delivery rewards, the NE Antenna hacking event, the NE Currency Trader, and various patrol events across all quadrants.

=== Lava Diamonds ===

Lava Diamonds are a rare Gamma currency found primarily in the SW quadrant. Known sources:
* SW Caves (primary source; ~39 diamonds per 1,800 KC)
* Lava Forts (variable reward; a single Fort may yield 60 Lava Diamonds but this reward has had bug history — verify in-game)
* Lava Temples

