=== True Guard ===

The [[True Guard]] from Talsia are also present in the Gamma NW quadrant. Unlike in Talsia where they are the apex threat, in Gamma they are a more manageable encounter — and notably, they now '''award Accolades''' upon defeat. True Guard in Gamma are primarily encountered in the NW and do not award TRP.

== Important Tips & Mechanics ==

; Speed is everything
: Unlike Talsia, Gamma does not reward "tank everything" builds. If enemies go first, they will drain your reactors and your bots will be defenceless. Priority: always go first or at minimum match enemy speed. Most [[Wasp]] enemies have ~225 speed; a squad that consistently goes before Wasps wins easily.

; Read everything
: Gamma is full of quest information, hint events, and lore scattered throughout patrol. Many quests are permanently gated on having read specific text events. Missing a Knight's name from an SE Outpost may require dozens more outpost visits (10% chance per outpost) to get another chance. Never fast-click through Gamma events.

; Mercs persist (and die permanently)
: Gamma mercs stay with the squad for the entire patrol — a huge advantage over Talsia. However, a bad fight that wipes your mercs means losing all the Accolades spent on them. Plan patrol carefully; don't risk valuable mercs on unnecessarily difficult encounters.

; Calling for reinforcements (SE) has a dark side
: When patrolling the SE, Controllers can call for patrol reinforcements. There is a 5% chance of receiving free mercs, but also a 35% chance of the call being intercepted — triggering an enemy ambush. Use this option judiciously.

; Note-taking is mandatory
: Quest information (Knight names, city names, door codes) is randomly generated per set and per account. There is no in-game journal. Write things down immediately upon encountering quest text. Missing this information is devastating: the Enhanced Reaper portal will not appear in the NE temple until the correct SE city name has been found, and the Brotherhood Outpost requires the exact door code.

== Endgame Goals ==
The following represent the overall goals of a Controller progressing through Gamma Sector across a set:

# '''Chassis collection''' — Hornet, Recon Hornet, Warthog, Recon Warthog, Flaming Hornet, Enhanced Reaper, Terminus Prototype, CyBulwark (where applicable)
# '''PMC Quest completion''' — complete the Brotherhood of the Chosen quest to obtain the [[Peace Maker Cannon]]
# '''SW Arena Masters''' — defeat the Carnutum Ignus Arena Masters to earn the [[Hydroplasmonic Reactor]]
# '''Meteorite Mining''' — accumulate significant tonnage for massive experience and Mirons (with full awareness of the 100-ton pirate aggression threshold)
# '''Trader items''' — acquire the [[Plutonium Core]], [[Hyper Drive]], [[Pneumatron]], and [[Rayden Device]] from the four quadrant traders
# '''Pirate Exterminator''' — reach 100 Pirate Corvette kills
# '''Space Cruiser Quest''' — complete the optional Space Cruiser bounty for its one-time cash reward

